(85, 'Discover to Recover', '2020 was indeed a tragic year! There was not much to accomplish due to the effect of the coronavirus. Those who survived the severity of the virus must be grateful to God Almighty that 2021 affords them another opportunity to recover what they had lost to Covid-19. Would you look forward to 2021 as a year of refreshing opportunities? It\'s never too late now to change your course of action.\r\n\r\nDon\'t settle for less despite how difficult things had been. Nothing in life is worth deserving without fighting for. Engage your dream, ambition, and vision and become a legend in your dispensation. You are transitioning to a moment to discover and recover, which ties to the principle of seeking and finding. Discover your true identity, and stop trying to become someone or something you are not. Otherwise, you may never see the good in yourself. Unless you discover, you won’t recover!\r\n\r\nMay I illustrate \'discover to recover\' by describing the functionalities of a computer Recycle Bin. We can draw from its dual operations – delete & recover – to teach a practical life lesson. As a computer end-user, I would mistakenly and initially delete a file and thought I had lost it forever. As my computer knowledge increased, I learned how to recover deleted files to the original directory. Sometimes, I may choose to delete the files finally from my computer memory. This example teaches that there’s hope for recovery.\r\n\r\nSee yourself as the best in your generation. Your failure to discover yourself could make it impossible if not difficult to recover from situations imposing stagnation, suppression, joblessness, poverty, poor health condition, non-achievements, etc. Based on your knowledge of the previous year’s challenges, primarily concentrate on the most important things you wish to do. Be strategic in advancing your plans for 2021.\r\n\r\nLife is not a competition but a contribution. Never be intimated by the progress and achievements of your peers or superiors. Be inspired and work hard to make your contributions. Never subject yourself to envying others. Arise to your potential! You know yourself better than anybody else. Don’t allow situation condition you to a place. Step forward and aim at your dreams and visions. Discover who you want to become in life and how you would like to contribute to society. You have the power to add value to yourself by improving in areas of limitations and becoming creative and innovative.\r\n\r\nA few years ago, Cemenco, a cement company in my country hired me as a nightshift contractor. I worked in a division/department called “Recycle.\" Today I guess it still exists! My team and I were obligated to repackage burst cement bags. When there was a scarcity of cement in the Liberian market, the Management would hire women to sweep the entire compound, pile, and collect the cement dust from the ground for repackaging.\r\n\r\nWe would pour the cement dust into a certain kind of machine and refill new cement bags. That was a recovery in action! Management could not afford to lose their valuable materials. They discovered higher production increase sales, generate revenues, and reduce scarcity in the market. Similarly, you should add value to yourself and be marketable in your dispensation. It\'s time to discover and recover!\r\n\r\nDespite your limitations, count on your strength to explore your potentials. Far beyond what men can imagine, God sees the best in you. Life is worth living when you can discover who you are and where you are going. Discover to recover ties to the principle of seeking and finding. 2021 is the beginning of recovery for those who are ready to take a journey of discovery.', 'blog-post-1.jpg', '', 60, 36, '2022-11-20 10:45:19'),
(86, 'What Moves God: Need or Faith?', 'One of my favorite American writers, Philip Yancey raised a contemporary theological issue admitting to complex suffering in a sinful and dying world and how God\'s silence to seemingly discouraged and disappointed Christians is a commonly asked question.\r\n\r\nHe posed the question, \"Where Is God When It Hurts?\" (2010) to examine why God seems to be silent. Yancey interrogated the level of God\'s intervention in people\'s situations. A similar question could be posed today because of COVID-19. Sorrows, excruciating pains, and fears were ever-increasing in the world due to the spread and effects of COVID-19.\r\n\r\nMany reputable, lovely, and potential people died because of this deadly pandemic. Old and young, black and white races are being affected. The death rate was escalating daily, thus leaving economies to crumble, families to starve, schools and universities to shut down, increasing the unemployment rate, and as well as, creating constant restrictions in religious worship centers amongst others.\r\n\r\nAn attempt to rephrase Philip Yancey\'s question is a needed challenge to inquire about what moves God to answer prayer – need or faith? An African writer presents an argument that I think compliment Yancey\'s question. Thompson J. Washington in, The Faith Factor, argues that \"God will not meet you at the point of your needs but the point of your faith.\"\r\n\r\nFew African Christians tend to believe the first statement. They consider Philippians 4:19, \"But my God shall supply all your need according to his riches in glory by Christ Jesus.\" In this verse, Paul did not indicate the condition by which believers could access the riches of God, except for assuring that God possesses heavenly blessings and has enriched his people (Ephesians 1:3).\r\n\r\nOn the contrary, those who believe that God moves based on faith tend to agree with Hebrews 11:6, \"But without faith, it is impossible to please him: for he that cometh to God must believe that he is and that he is a rewarded of them that diligently seek him.\" Washington believes that faith is a means by which God responds to us and it can be justified by citing God\'s miraculous moves in human history.\r\n\r\nA classic example is the story of Abram, whose name was changed to Abraham (Genesis 15:6). In Genesis 15, Abraham needed a son to continue his lineage and subsequently fulfill the promise of becoming the father of many nations. God recognized his need but could only act based on the level of Abraham\'s faith.\r\n\r\nWhen Abraham\'s faith in God was accounted as righteousness (v.6), all of his needs were addressed. Amid this COVID-19 global pandemic, Christians should continue to pray fervently to God through faith so he would meet their needs. Paul reminds the Christians, \"For we walk by faith, not by sight\" (2 Corinthians 5:7).\r\n\r\nRegardless of the situation confronting the lives of Christians, faith permits God to act. Even if Christians should cry out to God, it should be done in faith, not as if they are complaining about their situation. God knows all of our needs yet he responds through our faith to address our needs.\r\n\r\nFor instance, God heard the cry of the Israelites and acted immediately because they expressed faith (Exodus 3:7). Throughout the ministry of Jesus, faith was a requirement for salvation, healing, deliverance, and miracles. All of those who came to Jesus and testified had some level of faith.\r\n\r\nFaith is the opposite of fear. Fear creates doubts and unbelief. Regardless of the effects of Coronavirus, Christians should trust in the power of God for healing, and acknowledge Jesus as the master healer. In March 2020, Liberia\'s first Coronavirus case was recorded: Nathaniel Blama was the first affected COVID-19 patient.\r\n\r\nFollowing the second week in April, another government official was diagnosed positive of Coronavirus. These two government officials are Christians, and they trusted and hoped in God for recovery. People interceded for them and they survived the severity of Coronavirus (Acts 12:5).\r\n\r\nReflecting on these testimonies, I recognize the faith of those prayerful and faithful intercessors. Therefore, Christians who are disappointed with God must understand that faith is a binding human response to get God\'s attention and that it leads to hope. Even if everything seems to be lost, all is not lost, because faith in God can change a story incredibly!', 'blog-post-2.jpg', '', 71, 36, '2022-11-20 10:48:58'),
(87, 'Fathers, Take Up Responsibility!', 'Since 2007 the world began to experience a serious economic crisis, the family has been greatly affected, as fathers cannot afford provisions for the home and mothers are gradually assuming the responsibility of the fathers.\r\n\r\nA few years ago, I listened to an interview conducted with children at various gambling centers in my country, Liberia. Of all the responses gathered as to why they chose to gamble, a little child said, “We are in the street gambling because our fathers don’t have accounts for us.”\r\n\r\nMany children are vulnerably roaming the streets because fathers have failed to take responsibility for the welfare of the family. Some fathers have willingly become liabilities to the family because their wives are doing part-time or full-time jobs.\r\n\r\nAlthough the world is evolving, and mothers are securing job opportunities to help upkeep the financial status of the home, God never intended the mothers to be the sole winners of the home or family.\r\n\r\nGenesis account reveals that God placed Adam in authority to look after the garden, as a father ought to care for his family. He was the breadwinner for his wife. God could not expect Adam to depend on his wife for provision. Rather, God Himself was Adam\'s utmost provider!\r\n\r\nNowadays, however, things are steadily changing about parental role and responsibility in the home. Because of modernization and what is termed as “gender equity,” fathers are losing control of their responsibility in the home. I do support the concept of gender equity but disagree that mothers completely take the role of the fathers in the home.\r\n\r\nDesignated as the helpmeet by God, mothers are to get involved in bringing up the children and make significant contributions to upkeep the home. But fathers should realize they are the heads and therefore must assume their responsibility for the welfare of the family.\r\n\r\nWhen a father assumes the financial responsibility of his family, all other responsibilities like raising or disciplining children among others will fall into place. Children are sensitive to whether their fathers are capable of addressing their basic needs.\r\n\r\nFailure on the fathers’ part, some children would disrespect or disobey their fathers. In the case of the child mentioned earlier, he justified his bad habit because of his father’s irresponsibility. He probably felt that his father was incapable of addressing his needs.\r\n\r\nTo this end, I suppose that one of the major factors contributing to poverty in Africa is because fathers have refused to take up responsibility.\r\n\r\nAccording to the book, “Ye Fathers” David G. Burkholder observed that the definition of a father has been limited to someone who only brings forth children into the world; beyond this meaning, he further encouraged fathers to care for the welfare of the family. To take up financial responsibility in the home, I recommend fathers to do the following:\r\n\r\n1. Get a job and earn a salary that can sustain the family\r\nBefore God presented Eve to Adam as his wife, Adam had a job which assumed a responsibility “to dress and to keep the garden” (Genesis 2:15).Adam could not have easily survived in the garden if he had not cultivated it well to produce good harvests.\r\n\r\nSimilarly, it is wise to have something doing before engaging in marriage. If a man is already married and doesn’t have a job, it is wiser and safer for him as a father to go out and find a job that would sustain him and the family.\r\n\r\nNo matter how much love wives and children may have for the fathers, if these fathers are not meeting up with their domestic roles, it is likely that they would lose their respect and ruin their integrity both in the home and society at large.\r\n\r\n2. Handle the finances wisely to sustain the family\r\nFathers are to wisely use the resources for the family that comes to the home. Whatever comes to the fathers belongs to the home! I am obliged to say this because I have observed that not all irresponsible fathers are jobless.\r\n\r\nSome fathers have lucrative jobs but cruelly refused to support their family. Their children have become gamblers and beggars in the streets and their wives have to carry the burdens of the family.\r\n\r\nUndoubtedly, real fathers are blessings rather than burdens. They are not liabilities but great access. Considering this situation, fathers must take up responsibility in the home; and together the family would celebrate them as real fathers in our world.', 'blog-post-3.jpg', '', 73, 36, '2022-11-20 10:50:54'),
(88, 'The Need for Adequate Public Latrines in Liberia.', 'Owing to the philosophy, “population brings growth,” I have observed that development via population growth is not without a challenge. In Liberia, limited public toilet facilities pose a serious challenge to the health of the population and the development of the country.\r\n\r\nI suppose that low budgetary support and overpopulation are the causes of this problem. Since 2015 Liberia\'s population started rapidly growing and is now estimated at 5.06million (World Population Review, 2020). JMP 2017 report reveals, \"Less than 20% of Liberians do not have access to privately-owned latrines. About 42% of the population practice open defecation.\"\r\n\r\nThe government of Liberia and its development partners had been committed to ensuring environmental health and sustainability by implementing a series of measures towards achieving the MDGs (#7) and SDGs (#6). However, there are still, unresolved public health issues confronting the health sector, with which lack of adequate public toilets is paramount.\r\n\r\nAccording to All Africa Liberia (December 2018), some influential government officials promised Liberians the construction of thousands of public toilet facilities in Monrovia but the promise has not been fulfilled. According to the Water and Sanitation Program (2012), Liberia had lost 17. 5 million US Dollars annually due to poor sanitation as citizens are being affected by waterborne diseases and infections.\r\n\r\nThis expenditure claimed a high budgetary allocation and depleted Government saving. Contrary to the saying, \"prevention is better than cure,\" it is obvious that the Liberian Government spends more on curative health than preventive care. Liberia has a fewer on-street toilets to accommodate travelers and passers-by.\r\n\r\nAlmost all of the on-street latrines are privately-owned. Attendants charge high service fees. These privately-owned public latrines are built with makeshift structures, muds, and concrete blocks but have limited rooms to accommodate 3-5 people at once. Notwithstanding, the Government of Liberia has built only a few off-street public toilets in some urban and rural communities.\r\n\r\nMany people do not have private latrines in their households. They use buckets as toilets and empty them at night. This problem threatens and compromises the health of the public, particularly residents of slum communities, of which women and girls are mostly affected with chronic infections.\r\n\r\nThe provision of public latrines is a significant aspect of ensuring environmental sustainability and achieving Sustainable Development Goals #3 (Good Health and Well-being) and #6 (Clean Water and Sanitation). Increasing the adequacy of public toilets implement a sustainable sanitation program across Liberia for the creation of a healthy environment.\r\n\r\nTo mitigate the threat to a healthy environment posed by inadequate public toilet facilities across Liberia, particularly in urban communities, key ministries and agencies must implement these strategies:\r\n\r\n1. Increase the number of public toilets in slum communities and other former settlements for the prevention of waterborne diseases and infections and eradication of open defecation.\r\n\r\n2. Prioritize the need for budgetary supports to step-up its intervention by increasing access to public toilet facilities across the country.\r\n\r\n3. Collaborate with private managers or NGOs to have interest and invest in the construction of on-street toilet facilities.\r\n\r\n4. Create a maintenance team to manage the operation and usage of the public toilet facilities to ensure environmental sustainability and prevent ushers from waterborne diseases and infections.\r\n\r\n5. Plant a signpost at intersections or on the roadsides to help travelers find the public toilets. Place the signpost blocks or meters away from the toilets\' destination to enable people from other regions or localities to access the public toilet.\r\n\r\nIn conclusion, I would like to encourage private investors to take advantage of constructing on-street public toilets to ease the burden many Liberians are now facing. I think if the Government of Liberia has limited resources to prioritize this project, it would be welcoming for interested business individuals to study the case and remedy the situation.\r\n\r\nI assure whoever is interested will generate money from this project. Many Liberians cannot even access the limited existing toilet facilities constructed in communities. They would prefer using the on-street public toilet facilities, as long as they are clean and spacious.', 'blog-post-4.jpg', '', 77, 36, '2022-11-20 10:51:54'),
(89, 'Don’t Despise Your Small Beginnings!', 'The stories of great and successful people are often and widely read but with a little understanding of how they transitioned from not enough to more than enough. Almost all the celebrants we admire today had small beginnings. They didn’t reach the top overnight. Opportunities surrounded them from the little things they were committed to doing daily.\r\n\r\nThe road to success could be extremely difficult for those who want to get there quickly and easily but possible for people who are ready and willing to go through the required processes. Make sure to wisely use every opportunity available to you. Managing your small beginning now predicts how well you will handle bigger opportunities. All your wishes in life may not be fulfilled at once until you tackle them bit by bit.\r\n\r\nEmbrace the little things you are doing. They are bridges to cross you to an expected end. Even if nobody commends you, keep pushing and know that your labor is not in vain. At the appropriate time, God will use that little thing to announce you and people will be compelled to commend you on your success. Remember whatever you are doing now that seems little is the beginning of greatness. Don\'t despise your small beginning!\r\n\r\nBefore a tree grows bigger to bear flowers and fruits and be admired and fed upon, it must be first planted into the ground as a seed and after a while germinate to cause attraction and make provision. Similarly, your present condition is likened to this seed and you have to be patient to undergo the process of germination. As you climb the ladder to greatness, know that little is much when God is in it. It’s not how long you’ve been doing the same thing but how well.\r\n\r\nExpect an incredible result when you embrace your small beginning. Life is such that we have to experience small things before we see big things. Whether you are starting a new job that cannot fully sustain you or selling a type of product you are ashamed of, don\'t quit. You are almost to your breakthrough. Hold on to your current position until bigger opportunity is available to you.\r\n\r\nSome years ago, many Liberian women and girls were ashamed to sell on the streets. They depended on men for everything. Today, things have changed. I see potential and beautiful girls are selling cold water, sugar cane, cookies, and plastic bags on the streets of Monrovia.\r\n\r\nAlways be at your best at your small beginning. Few years ago, I didn’t despise my small beginnings. I sold on the streets, between cars, in video clubs, and other places. I was not ashamed of selling the least items because I had to assist my parents with provision in the home. At that time, women laughed at me, and called me all sort of names because I was carrying waiter on my head and holding bucket in my hand. I didn\'t care about their mockery. I was focused and pleased to help alleviate poverty from my family.\r\n\r\nHowbeit, I understood that the Liberian slogan “small, small” reinforces our courage and commitment to push forward in life regardless of our ups and downs. We should focus on doing the small things now and expect big things later.', 'little_beginng.jpg', '', 75, 36, '2022-11-20 10:55:08'),
(91, 'The change in women fashion clothing', 'The design upset happens when there is any development on the planet style industry. From the design world commencement, the ladies are spending more cash on their array as indicated by changing the design style.\r\n\r\nLadies design insurgency has element of a more prominent ability in changing the women fashion clothing. Ladies\' style attire industry never touches the retreat period as the insurgency happen when changes. A lady buys the garments, it doesn\'t make a difference that what is the states of the business sector.\r\n\r\nThe development dependably proceeds in the design business as it never winds up. In the event that you need to think about the 1920 insurgency time of womens fashion clothing then we must let you know that individuals from design world used to create lady dress by the nearby materials. In present manner world the garments creator has expansive worldwide materials for utilizing as a part of delivering the lady garments.\r\n\r\nThe polished, cutting edge and attractive look patterns are running at present in marked ladies\' dress and lady are acknowledging and purchasing these most recent womens fashion clothes. There are immense design brands in the business sector and all are given an alternate style to the lady attire.\r\n\r\nOn the off chance that you need to check the most recent brands upscale array of lady garments then you can see on the web. The unrest in the women fashion clothing world likewise gives a blast in the design business however it requires a lot of investment to come in pattern in a few nations.\r\n\r\nIn present days the stylish attire has turned into the first decision for young ladies. The upheaval proceeds in the elegant apparel for womens fashion clothing. The garments architects in the style business make diverse sorts of lady garments. The principal insurgency happens in the worldwide nations, then it achieves in household nations. At some point the style architects